                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.60C/92: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-15">September 15,
                            1939</date>.<lb/>[Received September 15—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. My 106, September 13, 5 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d623fn12">Not
                        printed.</note> I have received following telegram from Biddle from
                        Krzemieniec<note n="13" xml:id="d623fn13">In southeastern Poland.</note>
                    dated September 11, 11 a.m.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Embassy has been evacuated with Government from Warsaw. Cable address now
                        American Embassy Poland. Embassy unable at present time to communicate with
                        Consulate General which remains in Warsaw.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
